<mah:MetroWindow x:Class="RotaryConverter.HelpDialog"
                 xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
                 xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
                 xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
                 xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
                 xmlns:mah="clr-namespace:MahApps.Metro.Controls;assembly=MahApps.Metro"
                 Title="Rotary Converter Help"
                 ShowCloseButton="True"
                 Width="350"
                 SizeToContent="Height"
                 Padding="5"
                 WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner"
                 mc:Ignorable="d">
    <StackPanel>
        <RichTextBox IsReadOnly="true">
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16">How to measure Rotary Length</Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
            Attach your chuck-rotary to your laser. Using your control program (eg LightBurn), note the current position of the rotary axis.<LineBreak/>
            Make a clear mark on the chuck and another stable reference point such as the metal bracket holding the chuck.<LineBreak/>
            In your control program, move the rotary axis until it has made a full rotation and the marks are precisely aligned again.<LineBreak/>
            Note the current position of the rotary axis.<LineBreak/>
            Your Rotary Length is the absolute value of the current position minus the starting position of the axis.
            </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </RichTextBox>
    </StackPanel>
</mah:MetroWindow>